    "label": "Maps, Medicine, Cholera - Unit 4",
    "source": "TB1 - English Units 1-6",
    "kind": "TEXT",
    "text": "a) Answer the following questions about the text on page 52-53 (MCSE). Answer in one sentence, do not copy the text. 1) Why did a lot of workers want to move to towns in the 19th century ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 2) How long did it take to minute villages to become main industrial centres ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 3) Why were people obliged to live near their work place ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 4) What didn’t exist in the new slums ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 5) What did they begin to use in the 1840s ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 6) Why wasn’t it possible to produce efficient pipes massively ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 7) What became contaminated ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 8) What happened in 1854 ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 9) What did Dr John Snow observe ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 10) How did they solve the problem of epidemic ? ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… b) Ask questions to get the following answers. 1) Coal became the main raw material. ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 2) In the 19th century, Britain had to face massive changes. ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 3) Slums were built rapidly. ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 4) The metallurgists lacked the necessary knowledge to produce relevant pipes. ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 5) Many countries throughout the world need drinking water. ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 6) Diseases are often linked to sanitary conditions. ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 7) The epidemic died out because they improved the living conditions. ………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………… 8) John Snow carried out a thorough analysis. …………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………"
